definitions: intrusion into an area belonging to or affecting someone or something else

examples.text: the creeping impingement of the digital world into our lives

shortDefinitions: intrusion into area belonging to someone else

definitions: a painful condition caused by rubbing or pressure on a tendon, nerve, etc., by adjacent structures

examples.text: shoulder injuries in swimming are most often caused by impingement
he has been bothered by a nerve impingement in his neck

shortDefinitions: painful condition caused by rubbing on tendon, nerve, etc.
